<h2>Difficulty swallowing, Gum sores, Mouth sores and White patches inside mouth</h2>
<p>WebMD Symptom Checker helps you find the most common medical conditions indicated by the symptoms difficulty swallowing, gum sores, mouth sores and white patches inside mouth including Coxsackie virus infection, Canker sores, and Thrush (infants and children).</p>
<p>There  are 12 conditions  associated with difficulty swallowing, gum sores, mouth sores and white patches inside mouth. The links below will provide you with more detailed information on these medical conditions from the WebMD Symptom Checker and help provide a better understanding of causes and treatment of these related conditions.</p>
